Lyris:
The embers of campfire are now slowly dying. 

The birds and the woodfolks have gone to their rest; 

The stars, they are shining, their light gleaming oer us; 

O God of nature, grant to us a peaceful night.

All things shall perish from under the sky; 

Music alone shall live, music alone shall live, 

Music alone shall live, never shall die.

Footsteps on distant trail, 

Campward are bending; 

Wood fire and bubbling stew, 

Rich odours sending; 

Here is your hearts desire, 

Rest when your feet shall tire, 

Open air and pals and food and fire; 

Joy never ending. 

Camp fires are burning low, 

No longer leaping; 

Scouts sing their evening song, 

Shadows come creeping; 

Sun sinks below the west, 

Goodnight and may you rest, 

Blankets warm and by soft sounds caressed; 

Scouts all are sleeping.

Youth is calling as we climb; 

Open air and rain or shine; 

Youth is calling fair or fine. 

Oh, wholl come a-roving with me? 

Chorus: 

O la vie, oli, oli ish, ha ha ha, 

O la vie, oli, oli ish, ha ha ha, 

O la vie, oli, oli ish, ha ha ha, 

O la vie, oli, oli ish. 

Out along the highway clear; 

Stalwart friends and right good cheer; 

Friends whore not afraid to share; 

Oh, wholl come a-roving with me? 

Up the rugged mountain side; 

Winding path with careless stride; 

Through wild natures woodland wide. 

Oh, wholl come a-roving with me? 

Bed beneath the starry sky, 

Campfire glimmers closely by, 

Winds that whistle, pines that sigh, 

Oh, wholl come a-roving with me?

我願以信譽為誓, 竭盡所能; 

對神明, 對國家, 盡責任;

對別人, 要幫助; 

對規律, 必遵行.
